{
  "texts": [
    "The MCS includes mental health, roleemotional, social functioning, and vitality.",
    "We applied norm-based scoring to the calculated PCS and MCS to convert them to a score with an average of 50 and a standard deviation of 10.",
    "The total score for each index ranges from 0 to 100, and higher scores indicate better QOL [30].This study used three QOL indices (PCS, MCS, and total QOL [sum of PCS and MCS]).",
    "We defined a poor QOL group to establish a prediction model.",
    "Each of the three scores was divided into terciles, and a score below the lowest tercile was classified as low QOL, with any scores at or above the lowest tercile classified as high QOL."
  ]
}